                    },
                    "videos": [
                      {
                        "id": "89d8ed60-3af0-4a55-b54f-50f4f90d0e0e",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": "December 27th, 2019 "
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Brian Gitta"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_brian_gitta.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "Even though Malaria is a curable disease, for many regions it is still a huge problem. In 2018, there were over 400,000 deaths from malaria. In most cases the death is because of late diagnosis. \n<br/><br/>\nThe IT specialist Brian Gitta developed a device which is 15 times faster than current ways of doing diagnosis of malaria. The end goal is closing that gap between the hospitals and the patients to help saving many lives!\n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "03:06"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_brian_gitta_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "8e1d208b-3bed-4b93-9a38-bb4fc60174cf",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": " December 20th, 2019 "
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Topher White"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_topher_white.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "The rainforest of the Amazon during the past years, has been deforested by thousands of acres. The ecosystem is being destroyed, and It is the large black-market organizations that are just profiting immensely from the destruction of the forest, and local people do not benefit at all from this.\n<br/><br/>\nThe technologist Topher White with his team, developed a solar powered smartphone with a powerful microphone. They put these devices up in the trees and listen to the sounds of the forest. They capture all the sounds and analyze it. The system functions as an alarm which tells of people.\n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "02:52"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_topher_white_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "6736f570-2538-4648-80cf-ea9266eb3ae4",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": "December 13th, 2019 "
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Pablo Garcia Borboroglu"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_pablo_garcia_borboroglu.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "Over half of the 18 species of penguins that exist on this planet are considered threatened.  Climate changes, marine pollution and overfishing reduce dramatically food in proximity.\n<br/><br/>\nPablo Garcia Borboroglu, Biologist and Conservationist with his team decided to educate not only the nearby communities, they reached kids from all over the planet to helping and continuing the task of saving of the penguins.\n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "03:01"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_pablo_garcia_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "6b5d257f-0079-405d-831d-f2a7c23163f2",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": "December 6th, 2019 "
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Emma Camp"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_emma_camp.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "The researcher and explorer Emma Camp noticed several places where corals are managing to survive, despite extreme and hostile water conditions.\n<br/><br/>\nThe fact that corals are capable of doing that, is transforming our understanding of how corals can survive into the future. \n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "03:04"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_emma_camp_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "f28ba73b-8b80-4f59-b11c-c9499c3fe3a7",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": "November 29th, 2019 "
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Miranda Wang"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_miranda_wang.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "The molecular biologist and entrepreneur Miranda Wang developed technologies to recycle plastic waste and make from it, valuable new products.\n<br/><br/>\nWith her team, she has been developing a technology to take plastic and to break it down into valuable chemicals, materials that are biodegradable and can be used in everyday consumer products or even to building vehicles. \n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "02:55"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_miranda_wang_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "d6919e30-7237-4331-a81c-5a97fd65fd97",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": "November 22nd, 2019 "
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Krithi Karanth"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_krithi_karanth.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "The Indian scientist and conservationist Krithi Karanth with her team assist families in filing claims with the government so they get compensation for their losses to wildlife. \n<br/><br/>\nShe plans to run a conservation education program in 300 schools in high-conflict areas, reaching 20,000 children. She hopes this could become a model for community-based conservation worldwide for those living near wildlife.\n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "03:05"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_krithi_karanth_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "42d83c89-516a-4a4d-88bf-dca553a2bbee",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": "November 15th, 2019 "
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Joao Campos Silva"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_campos_silva.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "The Amazon underwent a period of intense exploitation due to the increasing demand for food and natural resources from the big cities.\n<br/><br/>\nThe fisheries ecologist João Campos-Silva succeeded in saving a species which was bound to extinction, and improving quality of life of rural populations through the management of the fish stocks. \n\n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "03:10"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_joao_campos_silva_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "41832ec8-f641-4cbb-bee7-ef5ad14f3287",
                        "fields": {
                          "date": {
                            "value": "November 8th, 2019"
                          },
                          "title": {
                            "value": "Grégoire Courtine"
                          },
                          "video": {
                            "value": "/data/media/video/partnerships/skai/rolex-org_skai_rae_gregoire_courtine.mp4"
                          },
                          "description": {
                            "value": "A great discovery initiated by the French researcher Gregoire Courtine, who succeeded in making paralyzed patients from an injury in their back, to walk again! \n<br/><br/>\nCourtine’s research goal is an implantable neuroprosthetic “bridge” between the patient’s brain and lumbar spinal cord, supported by wireless technology\n"
                          },
                          "duration": {
                            "value": "02:59"
                          },
                          "link": null,
                          "posterframe": {
                            "value": "/data/media/img/skai/rolex_org_skai_the_pioneers_who_shape_the_future_gregoire_courtine_posterframe_1920x1080.jpg"
                          }
                        }
                      }
                    ],
